text: Maite Teresa Andreu Rodríguez (born 26 January 1971) is a Spanish handball player. She was born in Almoradí, Spain. She competed at the 2004 Summer Olympics, where Spain finished 6th. ==References== Category:1971 births Category:Living people Category:Sportspeople from Alicante Category:Spanish handball players Category:Olympic handball players for Spain Category:Handball players at the 2004 Summer Olympics
